# Styling & UI — Padrões

## Tailwind CSS 4
- Usar classes utilitárias Tailwind — sem CSS modules ou styled-components
- Helper `cn()` de `@/lib/utils` para merge condicional de classes (clsx + tailwind-merge)

```tsx
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';

<div className={cn('p-4 rounded-lg', isActive && 'bg-blue-500', className)} />
```

## Tema claro/escuro
- Gerenciado por `ThemeContext` (`src/contexts/ThemeContext.tsx`)
- Toggle via `ThemeToggle` component
- Usar classes `dark:` do Tailwind para variantes escuras
- Cores de fundo: `bg-white dark:bg-gray-900`, `bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800`
- Texto: `text-gray-900 dark:text-white`, `text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400`
- Bordas: `border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700`

